    from IPython.display import HTML

In this notebook we call the created animations in the last notebook [(mapping the result.ipynb)](http://nbviewer.ipython.org/github/emunozh/visualizing-heat-demand-data/blob/master/2%20mapping%20the%20result.ipynb). This two notebook are separated from each other because the visualization of animations does not work well under python 3, at least on my machine. Therefor I have decided to create a new notebook and run it under python 2.7.


    def video(fname, mimetype):
        video_encoded = open(fname, "rb").read().encode("base64")
        video_tag = '<video controls alt="test" src="data:video/{0};base64,{1}">'.format(mimetype, video_encoded)
        return HTML(data=video_tag)
